For example:
    
    /**
     * In module M2
     */
    public class C2 {
    }    

    /**
     * In module M1, module M2 is within compile scope.
     */
    public class C1 {
      private C2;

      public String hello() {
        return &quot;hi&quot;;
      }
    }

    
    /**
     * Module M1 is in compile scope, M2 not visible.
     */
    @Test
    public void test() {
      C1 instance = org.mockito.Mockito.mock(C1.class);
    }

Running the above will result in:
   

    Underlying exception : java.lang.TypeNotPresentException: Type C2 not present

Of course, if the interface I1 for C1 is extracted and mocked by the test, then all is well because I1 has no reference to C2.

